Description: Micrus Endovascular develops implantable and disposable medical devices used in the treatment of cerebral vascular diseases.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Micrus Endovascular Corporation develops and manufactures both implantable and disposable medical devices used in the treatment of cerebral vascular diseases. Micrus Endovascular develops products that can be used by interventional neuroradiologists, interventional neurologists, and endovascularly trained neurosurgeons to treat both cerebral aneurysms responsible for hemorrhagic stroke and intracranial atherosclerosis, which may lead to ischemic stroke. The Micrus Endovascular product lines enable physicians to gain access to the brain in a minimally invasive manner through the vessels of the arterial system. Full Description: EStartAcademy.com will be the predominant provider of practical online entrepreneurial education in the United States and around the world.  By providing interactive video training, entrepreneurs will gain valuable, action-focused knowledge that can immediately help them start, run, and/or grow their businesses.  The entrepreneurial spirit is alive and well in the United States and around the world.  Sadly, however, this spirit is restrained by a lack of readily available, affordable education for entrepreneurs.  Existing and aspiring business owners can muddle through hundreds of thousands of books on various topics, or they can spend hundreds of thousands of dollars getting an MBA or other business degree - one that may or may not prepare them for the everyday demands and challenges of starting, running, marketing, financing, and growing a business.   EStartAcademy.com recognizes the void of entrepreneurial education available in a one stop shop.  Similarly, the Company also realizes that not all business owners are created equally.  Some have absolutely no fundamental business knowledge, while others are fairly proficient at many aspects of running a business, but they lack only certain skill sets, or wish to enhance their existing knowledge on a particular subject.  That's why eStartAcademy will offer Beginner, Intermediate, and Advanced level courses on most topics, including: starting a business, financing a business, marketing, operations, management, website development, business plan development, negotiations, law, and a variety of other topics.

Description: TherapyCharts offers an EHR system enabling psychologists to manage patient records and appointment schedules.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: TherapyCharts is an online mental health treatment planning EHR for psychology. TherapyCharts psychology focused work-flow helps solo and small practice psychologists stay on top of psychology best practices and insurance reporting requirements without the distraction of medical work-flow EHR systems.  The pitch to psychologists:  provide better care, save time and money, secure your records. The TherapyCharts online SaaS solution relieves psychologists of the cost and hassle of periodic software installations and upgrades, network upkeep, and patient record storage and maintenance. Because TherapyCharts features a psychology focused work-flow, all the information a psychologist needs is usually within one to three clicks away. Other mental Health EHR systems sell Psychologists (i.e. non-medical mental health practitioners) the same EHR system that they sell to Psychiatrists (i.e. medical mental health practitioners). However, workflow, best practices, and insurance requirements are not the same for Psychologists as they are for Psychiatrists. TherapyCharts differentiates itself from other Mental Health EHR treatment planning systems in the following ways: -TherapyCharts features an innovative web-based computer authorization system that allows therapists to access and work with patient records from any computer within minutes, without sacrificing HIPAA security. -TherapyCharts psychology focused work-flow clears away the clutter of medical based EHR. All the information a psychologist needs is usually within one or two clicks away. -TherapyCharts web based (SaaS) system reduces cost and hassle of installed based systems Psychology best practice standards are built-in and automatically kept up-to-date online -Insurance compliance standards are built-in and automatically kept up-to-date online - Simple flat rate affordable pricing

Description: Charleston, South Carolina
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Charleston, South Carolina is home to a highly successful entrepreneur by the name of Sam Mustafa. His efforts have revived the downtown area. He opened a number of award-winning restaurants. These replaced the old and unused buildings lining the streets. Now residents and visitors enjoy a livelier and more attractive area. His business efforts have breathed new life into the community. But long before he dressed the town in fresh destinations, he grew up with his five brothers in Kuwait. His pursuit of education is what brought him to America. Sam Mustafa enrolled at the University of Illinois to earn a degree in engineering. At first he found himself doing poorly in his classes. He was at a loss as to why his grades were suffering. So he decided he would pick up some part time work, to make him more responsible. He filled positions at Pizza Hut, McDonald’s, and Domino’s Pizza. All of these taught him a valuable lesson. He loved working in the food industry, but hated working for people. Sam Mustafa then earned enough money to rent a commercial space on campus. With Sam’s Café open for business, he finally found focus and drive. He very quickly earned his degree and a handsome sum of money. He had enough to increase his savings, buy more business space, and even send some home to Kuwait. After this he decided to take a vacation. He landed in Charleston, and realized this would be his new home. Sam Mustafa became the CEO of the Charleston Hospitality Group. Along with this and his entrepreneurial efforts in the Charleston area, the community was really coming together. He single-handedly turned many of the vacant, depressing buildings, and made them into attractive night spots. Sam Mustafa is now a dedicated Charlestonian, who gives back to the area every way he can. The downtown area wouldn’t be what it is today without him.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Food and Beverage, Real Estate, Travel and Tourism

Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: 4M Carbon Fiber Corp. ("4M"​), a Knoxville, Tennessee-based carbon-fiber technology company holds the exclusive rights to commercialize atmospheric plasma oxidation for the production of carbon fiber that was co-developed with Oak Ridge National Laboratory and RMX Technologies. 4M completed a reverse merger in 2017 with Woodland Holdings Corp., an SEC reporting company ("Woodland"​ or the "Company"​) to position itself as a public entity. 4M became a wholly-owned subsidiary of Woodland, through which Woodland will conduct its business operations. The company expects to be trading in late 2018. 4M recently determined that the best way to extract the economic and technical value from the technology is to build production lines using the technology and sell fiber. The technology has been proven to use 75% less energy, produce a high-quality fiber, and use 1/3 footprint for the same production capacity. These claims have been validated by multiple international carbon fiber producers. The company is in discussions with several of the world’s largest carbon fiber makers and a billion dollar per year international energy savings performance company to build five production lines in the next 5 years using the technology. The use of this technology is expected to reduce the cost of carbon fiber by 20%. The use of this technology is expected to reduce the cost of carbon fiber by a conservative 25%.
